  abstract = {Aims: We study the distribution and physical properties of molecular gas 
in the disc around the T Tauri star IM Lup on scales close to 200 AU. We
investigate how well the gas and dust distributions compare and work
towards a unified disc model that can explain both gas and dust
emission. Methods: 12CO, 13CO, and
C18O J=2-1 line emission, as well as the dust continuum at
1.3 mm, is observed at 1.8 arcsec resolution towards IM Lup using the
Submillimeter Array. A detailed disc model based on the dust emission is
tested against these observations with the aid of a molecular excitation
and radiative transfer code. Apparent discrepancies between the gas and
dust distribution are investigated by adopting simple modifications to
